&lt;p&gt;Hudson River Trading (HRT) is seeking a Deployment Engineer to join our global Systems and Network teams. In this role, you will help streamline our day-to-day data centre related work to ensure that HRT’s world-class trading environment remains resilient and high-performing. Based in Singapore, you will be on the front line for our global network infrastructure, taking ownership of maintaining the infrastructure that keeps HRT’s trading systems running 24/7.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This is an execution-focussed role that requires a get-it-done attitude and a high level of dependability. You will be responsible for hands-on infrastructure management, including hardware troubleshooting, data center deployment work and coordinating with remote hands. You will work closely with senior engineers to orchestrate deployments and resolve issues, providing an essential service allowing our engineering teams to scale.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The ideal candidate is a disciplined and proactive technologist who thrives in a high-stakes production environment. If you are a hard worker who enjoys the hands-on side of technology and is looking to make an impact within a premier global trading firm, we’d love to speak with you.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Responsibilities&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Act as the primary point of contact for remote hands and data center technicians to coordinate hardware installations and repairs&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Perform routine server and network hardware maintenance (e.g. troubleshooting, cabling work, component replacements, etc.)&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Ensure network circuits are operational, including implementing cross connects and troubleshooting with carriers on link issues&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Execute operating system installations and basic server configurations following detailed documentation&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Manage physical asset tracking and inventory across global data center locations&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Script basic solutions to automate routine checkups and operational reporting&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Work closely with the Trading Operations team to coordinate and execute scheduled maintenance activities&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Troubleshoot connectivity and hardware failures in a live production environment&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Qualifications&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;1–5 years of relevant experience in a hands-on technical role preferred&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Basic network administration skillset, including the ability to log in to switches, routers, and firewalls to run basic commands&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Fundamental understanding of Linux/UNIX command line tools and basic system administration&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Practical experience with hardware troubleshooting (Servers, NICs, SFPs, and different types of cabling)&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Familiarity with basic networking concepts and circuit troubleshooting&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Experience with shell scripting (Bash) or Python for basic task automation is a plus&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Ability to follow complex technical instructions with extreme attention to detail&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Comfort working outside of standard business hours (evenings/weekends) to support a global, 24-hour trading cycle&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Strong communication skills in order to provide clear updates to stakeholders across time zones&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;A disciplined approach to production environments&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Background in trading infrastructure teams or tech companies with significant data center footprint, is a plus&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;content-conclusion&quot;&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Culture&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span data-sheets-value=&quot;{&amp;quot;1&amp;quot;:2,&amp;quot;2&amp;quot;:&amp;quot;Hudson River Trading (HRT) brings a scientific approach to trading financial products. We have built one of the world&#39;s most sophisticated comput

&lt;p&gt;The Hardware team at Hudson River Trading (HRT) creates high performance compute engines using FPGA and ASIC technology to drive low latency trading decisions on global markets. We build custom solutions across the spectrum of speed and smarts: from bespoke circuits to world-class machine learning accelerators.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;These high performance designs require even higher performance verification. We are looking for experienced Design Verification (DV) engineers who are skilled at writing testbenches and building verification environments to exercise complex HDL. Our ideal candidate is not only an ace tester, but a practicing toolsmith. You know the EDA landscape and want to be part of a team actively working to rethink, redesign, and surpass the status quo. For example, members of our team are active maintainers of popular open source projects such as Slang, Verilator, and Cocotb.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;FPGA and ASIC verification is part of an innovative, growing team at HRT which is integral to the success of our trading. You can expect to always be challenged by the ever-changing financial markets as you work to ensure correctness and robustness of our critical hardware in an extremely fast-paced, real-time environment. No financial experience is necessary.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Responsibilities&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Creating testbenches and tests for our hardware platform, leveraging a hybrid open-source/proprietary, highly flexible environment&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Writing detailed verification plans&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Quickly root-cause RTL bugs&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Collaborating directly with designers for rapid bringup of new projects and debugging of existing designs&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Managing test suites and continuous integration infrastructure&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Developing and improving open-source and internal tools&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Qualifications&amp;nbsp;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Superb debug and analytical skills&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Professional experience (2+ years) in RTL functional verification for FPGA or ASIC&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Experience with code and functional coverage collection/analysis&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Experience with SystemVerilog and industry-standard frameworks such as UVM&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Experience with Python&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Comfortable in a Linux environment&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Familiarity with Verilator and/or Cocotb preferred&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;C++ experience is a plus&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;A bachelor’s degree in computer science, electrical engineering, or a related field&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The estimated base salary range for this position is 175,000 to 250,000 USD per year (or local equivalent). The base pay offered may vary depending on multiple individualized factors, including location, job-related knowledge, skills, and experience. This role will also be eligible for discretionary performance-based bonuses and a competitive benefits package.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;content-conclusion&quot;&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Culture&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
